race.comment: SPRINGER'S BOY (6) comes off a swift 25.36 placing at Shepparton over 450m. Smart effort latest and looks a key chance again here. WESTSIDE WIZARD (1) is struggling to break through but racing consistently, finishing in the minors three starts on end. Last time out flew the lids with a fast early sectional but gathered in and finished in the minors when third (25.54) at Shepparton over 450m. Racing well and deserves a win. PAW ULTRA (2) comes off an average performance last start when eighth at Sandown over 515m behind Colac Kid (29.97) in a Special conditions H. Was in the money prior to that. Goes well out of this box with a win and four minor placings. Has ability and a bold showing is expected.
